 1305–ABT 1420":"circa 1305–circa 1420","1305–1420":"1305–1420","1310–1377":"1310–1377","1325–1392":"1325–1392","1338–Female":"1338–Overleden","1340–Female":"1340–Overleden","1315–Female":"1315–Overleden","1340":"1340","ABT 1338":"circa 1338","1392":"1392","Abt 1305":"circa 1305","1338":"1338","1305":"1305","1315":"1315","1325":"1325","1377":"1377","ABT 1420":"circa 1420","1310":"1310","1420":"1420","1331":"1331","about 1340":"circa 1340","Devonshire, Devon, England":"Devon, England","Askham, Westmoreland, England":"Askham, Westmorland, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","England":"Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Askham, Eden district, Westmorland, England, United Kingdom":"Askham, Westmorland, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Askham, Westmorland, England":"Askham, Westmorland, England"},"en":{"Abt 1305–ABT 1420":"about 1305–about 1420","1305–1420":"1305–1420","1310–1377":"1310–1377","1325–1392":"1325–1392","1338–Female":"1338–Deceased","1340–Female":"1340–Deceased","1315–Female":"1315–Deceased","1340":"1340","ABT 1338":"about 1338","1392":"1392","Abt 1305":"about 1305","1338":"1338","1305":"1305","1315":"1315","1325":"1325","1377":"1377","ABT 1420":"about 1420","1310":"1310","1420":"1420","1331":"1331","about 1340":"about 1340","Devonshire, Devon, England":"Devon, England","Askham, Westmoreland, England":"Askham, Westmorland, England, United Kingdom","England":"England, United Kingdom","Askham, Eden district, Westmorland, England, United Kingdom":"Askham, Westmorland, England, United Kingdom","Askham, Westmorland, England":"Askham, Westmorland, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"English","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English, Scottish, and Welsh: ethnic name from Middle English <i>English</i>, <i>Inglish</i>, <i>Inglis</i> ‘English’ (Old English <i>Englisc</i>), sometimes alternating with Anglo-Norman French <i>Engleis</i>, <i>Engles</i>, <i>Anglais</i>, <i>Angles</i> (Old French <i>Englois</i>). Compare   Inglis   and   England  . Among the aristocracy and upper gentry it marked out a man of English ancestry from one of Norman or continental origin. In counties bordering England with Scotland and Wales the name distinguished an Englishman from a Scot or a native Welshman on both sides of the border. The name may also have been acquired by English merchants who traded abroad or who lived and worked in a ‘French’ borough in England (one exclusively administered by Normans).","Irish: in Ireland, this name was used to denote an Englishman, often being adopted for Irish <b>Aingléis</b> ‘Englishman’ or through mistranslation for <b>Mac an Ghallóglaigh</b>, see   Gallogly   and   Golightly  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Engles","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Michel, Remi.","English and Scottish: variant of   English   or   Inglis  .","Altered form of German and Dutch   Engels  ."]},{"name":"Inglis","meanings":["Scottish (Lanarkshire and Midlothian): ethnic name from Scots <i>Inglis</i> ‘English(man)’. Compare   English  ."]},{"name":"England","meanings":["English: habitational name from Middle English <i>Engelond</i> ‘England’. It was probably a formal alternative to   English  , which is also well evidenced as a surname in England. These names may have been acquired by English landowners who moved in Norman social circles or who lived in a neighbouring country (Scotland, Wales, or Ireland), or by English merchants who traded abroad.","Norwegian: habitational name from any of various farmsteads so named, from Old Norse <i>eng</i> ‘meadow’ + <i>land</i> ‘land’.","Swedish: ornamental name with the same meaning as 2."]}]},{"name":"Idonea","type":"FIRST","meanings":["An old baptismal name derived from Latin idoneus, fit, meet, proper."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Idonea Lengleys English was born about 1305 as the daughter of Alice de Kirkbride. She married Edmund Sandford in 1331, in Askham, Westmorland, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. She died about 1420, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 117."},"et":{"Abt 1305–ABT 1420":"umbes 1305–umbes 1420","1305–1420":"1305–1420","1310–1377":"1310–1377","1325–1392":"1325–1392","1338–Female":"1338–Surnud","1340–Female":"1340–Surnud","1315–Female":"1315–Surnud","1340":"1340","ABT 1338":"umbes 1338","1392":"1392","Abt 1305":"umbes 1305","1338":"1338","1305":"1305","1315":"1315","1325":"1325","1377":"1377","ABT 1420":"umbes 1420","1310":"1310","1420":"1420","1331":"1331","about 1340":"umbes 1340","Devonshire, Devon, England":"Devon, England","Askham, Westmoreland, England":"Askham, Westmorland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Askham, Eden district, Westmorland, England, United Kingdom":"Askham, Westmorland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Askham, Westmorland, England":"Askham, Westmorland, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1305–ABT 1420":"noin 1305–noin 1420","1305–1420":"1305–1420","1310–1377":"1310–1377","1325–1392":"1325–1392","1338–Female":"1338–Kuollut","1340–Female":"1340–Kuollut","1315–Female":"1315–Kuollut","1340":"1340","ABT 1338":"noin 1338","1392":"1392","Abt 1305":"noin 1305","1338":"1338","1305":"1305","1315":"1315","1325":"1325","1377":"1377","ABT 1420":"noin 1420","1310":"1310","1420":"1420","1331":"1331","about 1340":"noin 1340","Devonshire, Devon, England":"Devon, England","Askham, Westmoreland, England":"Askham, Westmorland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Askham, Eden district, Westmorland, England, United Kingdom":"Askham, Westmorland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Askham, Westmorland, England":"Askham, Westmorland, England"},"fr":{"Abt 1305–ABT 1420":"environ 1305–environ 1420","1305–1420":"1305–1420","1310–1377":"1310–1377","1325–1392":"1325–1392","1338–Female":"1338–Décédée","1340–Female":"1340–Décédée","1315–Female":"1315–Décédée","1340":"1340","ABT 1338":"environ 1338","1392":"1392","Abt 1305":"environ 1305","1338":